fromMMPMParameterType

public static java.lang.Class fromMMPMParameterType(gatech.mmpm.ActionParameterType type)
Given a MMPM parameter type, this method returns a Class object representing such a type. MMPM has some built-in types that are not present in Java, so a conversion must be performed. The conversion is performed as follows: 
 if (type == ActionParameterType.BOOLEAN) {
        return Boolean.class;
 } else if (type == ActionParameterType.ENTITY_ID) {
        return String.class;
 } else if (type == ActionParameterType.ENTITY_TYPE) {
        return String.class;
 } else if (type == ActionParameterType.FLOAT) {
        return Float.class;
 } else if (type == ActionParameterType.INTEGER) {
        return Integer.class;
 } else if (type == ActionParameterType.STRING) {
        return String.class;
 } else if (type == ActionParameterType.PLAYER) {
        return String.class;
 } else if (type == ActionParameterType.COORDINATE) {
        return float[].class;
 } else if (type == ActionParameterType.DIRECTION) {
        return Integer.class;
 } else if (type == ActionParameterType.OBJECT) {
        return Object.class;
 }
If the input type is not recognized, an exception is thrown.

Parameters:
type - the type to be converted.
Returns:
a Class object representing the type type.

addDirectorySeparator

public static java.lang.String addDirectorySeparator(java.lang.String directory)
If a directory name does not contain the separator character at the very end, it is added. Otherwise, the same input directory is returned.

overwrites

public static java.lang.String overwrites(java.lang.String fileName)
Checks if a file name already exists in the file system. If so, returns a new file name based on fileName, which represents a file that does not exist in the file system (the name is the same as fileName except for the fact that is has been appended a number at its end, before the file extension).

removeExtension

public static java.lang.String removeExtension(java.lang.String fileName)
Removes the extension from a file name. If the file name has no extension, it is left unchanged.

getExtension

public static java.lang.String getExtension(java.lang.String fileName)
Returns the extension of a file name, or null if it has none.

removeDirectorySeparator

public static java.lang.String removeDirectorySeparator(java.lang.String directory)
If a directory name contains the separator character at the very end, it is removed. Otherwise, the same input directory is returned.

format
